<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36071g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36071g">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36071g"> 71(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> going to Adam &amp; Eve</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">At this period &hellip; the Penal Laws were in full vigour against the Roman Catholics. &hellip; <font color="green">[therefore a priest or friar]</font> would not allow any person to pass into the private chapel except those whom he knew to be Roman Catholics, and all such persons had, as a pass or countersign, to use the expression, &ldquo;I am <mark>going to Adam and Eve</mark>.&rdquo; <small> James Collins, <a name="JCLO" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCLO"><cite title="source">Life in Old Dublin</cite></a> (l913) 112</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
